1
00:00:10,153 --> 00:00:13,306
(Previous Chapter) You know the
kids here aren't like normal kids.

2
00:00:13,819 --> 00:00:15,481
Look after our new friend, Tanrak.

3
00:00:15,691 --> 00:00:16,417
I'm Barth.
Like basketball?

4
00:00:17,446 --> 00:00:19,322
Like the saint. Bartholomew.

5
00:00:19,646 --> 00:00:22,086
It's Grade 12, second term,
and you still got in?

6
00:00:22,711 --> 00:00:23,951
What are you gonna do about it?

7
00:00:25,030 --> 00:00:26,704
Barth! Barth! Barth!

8
00:00:26,958 --> 00:00:29,291
But if you keep behaving like this,

9
00:00:29,761 --> 00:00:31,840
I'll have to ask you to leave the school.

10
00:00:32,177 --> 00:00:33,480
Do you really believe in God?

11
00:00:33,823 --> 00:00:35,200
I believe God is real.

12
00:00:35,594 --> 00:00:39,262
I believe my parents are with Him up there.

13
00:00:39,743 --> 00:00:43,230
Maybe my God isn't as kind as yours.

14
00:00:48,920 --> 00:00:51,040
“WHAT MAN AMONG YOU
HAVING A HUNDRED SHEEP

15
00:00:51,065 --> 00:00:52,840
AND LOSING ONE OF THEM

16
00:00:52,865 --> 00:00:55,151
WOULD NOT LEAVE THE
NINETY-NINE IN THE DESERT

17
00:00:55,176 --> 00:00:57,462
AND GO AFTER THE LOST
ONE UNTIL HE FINDS IT?”

18
00:00:57,487 --> 00:00:59,264
(LUKE 15:4)

19
00:01:03,709 --> 00:01:05,389
Alright, let's go home.

20
00:01:05,756 --> 00:01:06,959
Always causing trouble.

21
00:01:13,558 --> 00:01:14,558
Sit down.

22
00:01:25,460 --> 00:01:27,727
Kongkit was wrong for starting it,

23
00:01:28,698 --> 00:01:30,698
but you two were at fault too.

24
00:01:32,891 --> 00:01:34,440
He was just trying to help me, Father.

25
00:01:36,311 --> 00:01:38,360
It's good to be kind,

26
00:01:39,120 --> 00:01:40,520
but for something this serious,

27
00:01:40,609 --> 00:01:43,221
you should've told me or Master Phak,

28
00:01:43,614 --> 00:01:45,720
not help each other hide it.

29
00:01:47,227 --> 00:01:48,974
What if it had gotten worse?

30
00:01:49,499 --> 00:01:50,571
What would you do then?

31
00:01:53,081 --> 00:01:54,521
I'm sorry, Father.

32
00:02:01,200 --> 00:02:02,200
Barth.

33
00:02:02,850 --> 00:02:03,913
You can go now.

34
00:02:19,122 --> 00:02:22,640
I trusted you to look after the new boy.

35
00:02:23,516 --> 00:02:26,485
I thought you could've handled
this better, Tanrak.

36
00:02:28,729 --> 00:02:30,160
I'm really sorry.

37
00:02:33,739 --> 00:02:34,739
From now on,

38
00:02:35,300 --> 00:02:37,591
I hope you'll take better care of him.

39
00:02:38,784 --> 00:02:39,880
I'm counting on you.

40
00:02:43,149 --> 00:02:44,149
Yes, Father.

41
00:02:48,144 --> 00:02:49,278
Please excuse me.

42
00:03:11,120 --> 00:03:15,585
SCHOLARSHIP STUDENT REPORT BOOK

43
00:04:14,000 --> 00:04:19,500
"Ticket to Heaven"
(Episode 2)

44
00:04:19,600 --> 00:04:21,777
ANGER IS QUELLED BY PATIENCE.

45
00:04:35,386 --> 00:04:37,257
What are you doing here all alone,
so studious?

46
00:04:43,350 --> 00:04:45,075
I'm not studying. I'm being punished.

47
00:04:46,278 --> 00:04:47,278
Master Phak.

48
00:04:50,678 --> 00:04:51,718
Just call me P'Phak.

49
00:04:52,521 --> 00:04:53,995
We're only a few years apart.

50
00:04:54,787 --> 00:04:56,310
No need to be so formal all the time.

51
00:05:07,488 --> 00:05:10,279
Hey, if you're being punished,
take it seriously.

52
00:05:11,636 --> 00:05:12,826
Maybe using up the whole book

53
00:05:13,392 --> 00:05:14,565
will teach you a lesson.

54
00:05:18,126 --> 00:05:19,620
I still don't know what I did wrong.

55
00:05:20,868 --> 00:05:22,990
Making me write hundreds of lines
won't change that.

56
00:05:27,506 --> 00:05:30,524
P'Phak! Come play with us.
We're one short.

57
00:05:30,751 --> 00:05:31,808
Yeah, I'll be right there.

58
00:05:31,942 --> 00:05:33,640
Okay. Hurry.

59
00:05:36,848 --> 00:05:38,761
Hey, can you play football?

60
00:05:42,270 --> 00:05:45,288
Yeah, but I… don't know anyone.

61
00:05:46,540 --> 00:05:47,540
So what?

62
00:05:48,101 --> 00:05:49,493
You're gonna be here for a year.

63
00:05:50,383 --> 00:05:51,818
Don't you plan to make any friends?

64
00:05:57,594 --> 00:05:59,840
Well, join me if you wanna play.

65
00:06:03,206 --> 00:06:04,206
Here I come.

66
00:06:18,702 --> 00:06:24,572
Lord, bless us and this food
we are about to receive.

67
00:06:24,841 --> 00:06:27,640
In the name of the Father, and of the Son,
and of the Holy Spirit.

68
00:06:28,194 --> 00:06:29,194
Amen.

69
00:06:48,937 --> 00:06:49,937
Up to you.

70
00:06:53,300 --> 00:06:54,300
Barth.

71
00:07:30,523 --> 00:07:31,680
I can sit somewhere else.

72
00:07:32,670 --> 00:07:34,880
Sit here. I was just kidding.

73
00:07:36,890 --> 00:07:38,440
Why would you sit by the trash can?

74
00:07:39,322 --> 00:07:40,322
Sit here.

75
00:07:47,327 --> 00:07:49,996
You know all these kids

76
00:07:50,324 --> 00:07:51,705
are scared that you'll punch them?

77
00:07:53,546 --> 00:07:55,279
But I'm not scared of you.

78
00:07:56,689 --> 00:07:58,259
Because God teaches us…

79
00:07:59,687 --> 00:08:02,586
Love your neighbor as yourself.

80
00:08:03,848 --> 00:08:05,287
Damn!

81
00:08:06,992 --> 00:08:07,992
Hey, Kong.

82
00:08:08,294 --> 00:08:10,200
Have you ever been punched
by your neighbor?

83
00:08:11,333 --> 00:08:12,706
You're about to get punched by me.

84
00:08:13,697 --> 00:08:14,817
Eat your food.

85
00:08:16,751 --> 00:08:17,751
Well.

86
00:08:17,832 --> 00:08:18,952
So is it true?

87
00:08:19,341 --> 00:08:21,040
You knocked out a guy at your old school

88
00:08:21,331 --> 00:08:22,341
with one punch?

89
00:08:24,839 --> 00:08:25,839
Yeah.

90
00:08:26,461 --> 00:08:28,600
Damn, a real boxer's move.

91
00:08:32,892 --> 00:08:34,280
So if I piss you off,

92
00:08:34,707 --> 00:08:35,711
will you punch me?

93
00:08:53,694 --> 00:08:54,734
Just kidding.

94
00:09:13,488 --> 00:09:14,488
Barth.

95
00:09:15,579 --> 00:09:17,057
Were you mad about them teasing you?

96
00:09:19,732 --> 00:09:20,732
No.

97
00:09:21,897 --> 00:09:22,985
I didn't care. Why?

98
00:09:24,817 --> 00:09:27,520
If you don't like it, I can tell them.

99
00:09:28,075 --> 00:09:29,400
So there won't be any trouble.

100
00:10:17,593 --> 00:10:21,049
Tanrak, return these catechism notebooks
to Class 12/1.

101
00:10:22,955 --> 00:10:25,088
Did I... get full marks, Master?

102
00:10:25,298 --> 00:10:27,400
Well, open it and see.

103
00:10:27,766 --> 00:10:30,840
Tell anyone who got less than half
to come see me next Tuesday.

104
00:10:31,932 --> 00:10:33,252
- Yes, Master.
- I'm off to class.

105
00:10:33,572 --> 00:10:34,593
Goodbye, Master.

106
00:10:52,591 --> 00:10:53,951
BODIN TUNGWONGWAT

107
00:11:05,707 --> 00:11:08,200
Here, Chris. Collecting full marks, huh?

108
00:11:08,777 --> 00:11:09,777
Not really.

109
00:11:10,929 --> 00:11:11,931
This one's yours.

110
00:11:28,129 --> 00:11:29,409
Can I move here?

111
00:11:32,747 --> 00:11:33,925
I can't see the board at all.

112
00:11:36,292 --> 00:11:38,825
That's Kongdech's seat. Ask him first.

113
00:11:42,473 --> 00:11:43,673
Can I sit here?

114
00:11:47,389 --> 00:11:48,389
Yeah, sure.

115
00:11:49,207 --> 00:11:50,592
As long as you do well in class.

116
00:12:05,194 --> 00:12:06,204
All right, everyone.

117
00:12:06,254 --> 00:12:07,992
Don't rush home after class.

118
00:12:08,155 --> 00:12:10,918
Go sign up for this year's Christmas
activity groups.

119
00:12:11,202 --> 00:12:14,403
Scholarship students without a group
can stay in the same group as last year.

120
00:12:19,246 --> 00:12:21,266
Do we have to do something
for the Christmas party?

121
00:12:23,984 --> 00:12:24,984
Of course.

122
00:12:30,693 --> 00:12:31,715
What do you like doing?

123
00:12:37,160 --> 00:12:38,200
I don't know.

124
00:12:40,533 --> 00:12:41,840
I don't like doing anything.

125
00:12:42,958 --> 00:12:44,040
Do I really have to?

126
00:12:45,646 --> 00:12:48,312
Yes, especially as scholarship students.

127
00:12:49,049 --> 00:12:51,096
We have to help out. We have duties.

128
00:12:53,139 --> 00:12:54,697
Oh, Bodin, you don't have a group yet.

129
00:12:54,808 --> 00:12:56,079
Join the reception team.

130
00:12:56,659 --> 00:12:58,087
If you don't remember your group,

131
00:12:58,112 --> 00:13:00,280
come check the list with me later.

132
00:13:04,204 --> 00:13:05,285
What group are you in?

133
00:13:06,303 --> 00:13:09,284
Hm? I'm in the choir.

134
00:13:09,595 --> 00:13:10,618
I'll join you.

135
00:13:13,703 --> 00:13:14,703
You can't.

136
00:13:15,237 --> 00:13:17,637
Since you don't like doing anything,

137
00:13:18,216 --> 00:13:20,080
I think the reception team suits you.

138
00:13:20,707 --> 00:13:21,766
You won't have to do much.

139
00:13:23,345 --> 00:13:24,345
No.

140
00:13:25,373 --> 00:13:28,376
I don't have any friends.

141
00:13:29,016 --> 00:13:30,125
You're the only one I know.

142
00:13:38,037 --> 00:13:39,480
You'll get to know more people

143
00:13:40,610 --> 00:13:41,971
once you start working with them.

144
00:14:24,857 --> 00:14:25,862
What are you doing?

145
00:14:35,789 --> 00:14:37,095
Do you pray like this every day?

146
00:14:39,890 --> 00:14:40,890
No.

147
00:14:41,340 --> 00:14:43,523
I'm here to pray for redemption.

148
00:14:46,747 --> 00:14:49,640
Redemption? For what?

149
00:14:57,312 --> 00:15:01,760
Well, I was partly at fault
for what happened to you,

150
00:15:02,815 --> 00:15:04,360
like Father said.

151
00:15:09,532 --> 00:15:11,257
The only wrong thing
you did was to help me,

152
00:15:11,281 --> 00:15:12,505
and now you're screwed too.

153
00:15:19,131 --> 00:15:20,280
Don't help me next time.

154
00:15:24,130 --> 00:15:26,160
If you feel bad,

155
00:15:27,429 --> 00:15:30,413
then pass your catechism test.

156
00:15:31,586 --> 00:15:35,280
Father assigned me to be your buddy.

157
00:15:37,306 --> 00:15:38,306
Okay?

158
00:15:40,105 --> 00:15:41,120
Then tutor me.

159
00:15:42,670 --> 00:15:43,814
Why should I tutor you?

160
00:15:44,844 --> 00:15:45,904
Because we're friends.

161
00:15:51,108 --> 00:15:52,149
Since when are we friends?

162
00:16:20,292 --> 00:16:24,760
Barth, can you stop breaking the rules?

163
00:16:25,706 --> 00:16:27,639
I'm gonna get in trouble too.

164
00:16:31,770 --> 00:16:33,877
I didn't see any sign saying
I couldn't leave school.

165
00:16:36,393 --> 00:16:37,920
It's a Magdalene House rule.

166
00:16:44,906 --> 00:16:45,906
Next,

167
00:16:47,801 --> 00:16:52,840
lust means letting desire control us.

168
00:16:54,007 --> 00:16:56,920
What if you can't stop it?

169
00:17:01,075 --> 00:17:02,090
Then you fight it.

170
00:17:06,773 --> 00:17:07,813
Why fight it?

171
00:17:08,924 --> 00:17:10,876
Have you tried this roti
in front of the school?

172
00:17:18,419 --> 00:17:19,689
Go off topic again,

173
00:17:20,027 --> 00:17:22,760
and I won't tutor you anymore.

174
00:17:25,382 --> 00:17:26,382
Yes, sir.

175
00:17:33,694 --> 00:17:34,694
Want some?

176
00:17:35,857 --> 00:17:36,857
Come on.

177
00:17:38,063 --> 00:17:39,065
Just a bite.

178
00:17:57,081 --> 00:18:00,040
Hurry up or I'll be
late for evening prayer.

179
00:18:05,393 --> 00:18:07,001
Let me see.
What are you even looking at?

180
00:18:09,926 --> 00:18:11,120
There are three people.

181
00:18:11,214 --> 00:18:13,096
The Believer, the Lover, and the Lost One.

182
00:18:13,812 --> 00:18:16,120
One always tells the truth.

183
00:18:16,403 --> 00:18:18,520
One sometimes tells the truth
and sometimes lies.

184
00:18:19,276 --> 00:18:20,876
And one always lies.

185
00:18:21,458 --> 00:18:23,720
The Believer says
the Lover always tells the truth.

186
00:18:24,128 --> 00:18:26,400
The Lover says
the Lost One always lies.

187
00:18:27,254 --> 00:18:29,920
The Lost One says
the Believer doesn't always tell the truth.

188
00:18:33,584 --> 00:18:37,584
So which one lies
and which one tells the truth?

189
00:18:51,169 --> 00:18:52,169
Seriously?

190
00:18:53,014 --> 00:18:54,406
Isn't your life stressful enough?

191
00:18:55,350 --> 00:18:56,571
Why are you doing this stuff?

192
00:19:00,789 --> 00:19:01,854
None of your business.

193
00:19:10,789 --> 00:19:12,294
Okay. Off you go, everyone.

194
00:19:17,578 --> 00:19:18,698
Kong, come on.

195
00:19:38,729 --> 00:19:40,023
RECEPTION TEAM

196
00:19:46,306 --> 00:19:47,306
Pairat.

197
00:19:47,418 --> 00:19:48,418
Yes.

198
00:19:48,664 --> 00:19:49,528
Korawit.

199
00:19:49,589 --> 00:19:50,589
Here.

200
00:19:51,156 --> 00:19:52,156
Bodin.

201
00:19:53,650 --> 00:19:54,650
Bodin.

202
00:19:57,738 --> 00:19:58,858
Where's Bodin?

203
00:19:59,191 --> 00:20:00,191
No idea.

204
00:20:00,628 --> 00:20:05,713
♪ Angels we have heard on high ♪

205
00:20:05,862 --> 00:20:10,230
♪ Sweetly singing o'er the plains ♪

206
00:20:10,677 --> 00:20:15,818
♪ And the mountains in reply ♪

207
00:20:15,967 --> 00:20:20,497
♪ Echoing their joyous strains ♪

208
00:20:21,108 --> 00:20:29,108
♪ Gloria in excelsis Deo ♪

209
00:20:39,806 --> 00:20:40,976
Are you looking for someone?

210
00:20:44,447 --> 00:20:45,447
Well…

211
00:20:47,343 --> 00:20:49,587
Someone told me I was in this group.

212
00:20:51,293 --> 00:20:52,302
My name's Bodin.

213
00:20:53,777 --> 00:20:54,777
Really?

214
00:20:58,857 --> 00:21:00,280
It's not here. There's no Bodin.

215
00:21:05,312 --> 00:21:08,182
They said they asked Tanrak
to pass on the message.

216
00:21:15,434 --> 00:21:16,440
What's going on, Tanrak?

217
00:21:22,128 --> 00:21:24,921
I forgot. Sorry, Master.

218
00:21:25,751 --> 00:21:28,800
That's okay. Can you sing?

219
00:21:32,704 --> 00:21:34,880
If I can't, can I help
carry things instead?

220
00:21:36,888 --> 00:21:38,518
We all have to help carry things anyway.

221
00:21:38,731 --> 00:21:41,440
All right. Let's hear you sing first.

222
00:21:41,902 --> 00:21:43,208
Maybe we'll get a new member.

223
00:21:44,502 --> 00:21:45,622
Come up front.

224
00:21:46,214 --> 00:21:47,253
Put your bag down.

225
00:21:48,903 --> 00:21:49,903
What song?

226
00:21:50,352 --> 00:21:51,623
I'll have someone play for you.

227
00:21:52,081 --> 00:21:53,121
“Before,” please.

228
00:21:53,481 --> 00:21:54,600
“Before” by Modern Dog?

229
00:21:54,927 --> 00:21:55,927
Yes.

230
00:21:56,176 --> 00:21:57,176
Okay.

231
00:21:58,432 --> 00:21:59,600
Give him the chords.

232
00:22:00,929 --> 00:22:01,945
Something like this.

233
00:22:04,919 --> 00:22:08,607
♪ My heart had had no one ♪

234
00:22:09,208 --> 00:22:12,080
♪ Until your love entered ♪

235
00:22:12,373 --> 00:22:17,120
♪ Filling my eyes bright with colors ♪

236
00:22:17,681 --> 00:22:21,160
♪ My side had had no one ♪

237
00:22:21,537 --> 00:22:24,400
♪ Until your love had mercy ♪

238
00:22:25,016 --> 00:22:29,360
♪ To empower me to keep going ♪

239
00:22:29,905 --> 00:22:37,905
♪ In this cruel world ♪

240
00:22:42,462 --> 00:22:43,760
Okay. Wow, that was great!

241
00:22:43,798 --> 00:22:44,840
Give him a hand.

242
00:22:48,661 --> 00:22:49,680
You sing well.

243
00:22:51,728 --> 00:22:53,080
In that case,

244
00:22:53,480 --> 00:22:55,800
you can have the same part as Tanrak.

245
00:22:56,502 --> 00:22:57,960
He can help train you.

246
00:22:58,732 --> 00:23:00,240
I'm counting on you, Tanrak.

247
00:23:00,533 --> 00:23:01,341
Okay.

248
00:23:01,384 --> 00:23:02,678
Go on. Have a seat.

249
00:23:03,457 --> 00:23:04,466
That chair is fine.

250
00:23:06,276 --> 00:23:08,720
You know the song we're rehearsing, right?

251
00:23:09,577 --> 00:23:10,333
Yes.

252
00:23:10,400 --> 00:23:12,684
Good. Then let's go again, everyone.

253
00:23:13,260 --> 00:23:21,260
♪ Gloria in excelsis Deo ♪

254
00:23:28,501 --> 00:23:34,452
♪ Gloria in excelsis Deo ♪

255
00:23:40,636 --> 00:23:43,177
Tanrak, tidy up the
room and lock it for me.

256
00:23:43,817 --> 00:23:44,817
Yes, Master.

257
00:23:45,267 --> 00:23:46,276
Bodin, help him out.

258
00:23:46,349 --> 00:23:47,349
Yes.

259
00:24:00,638 --> 00:24:01,638
Who's this?

260
00:24:04,585 --> 00:24:05,921
Saint Cecilia.

261
00:24:10,395 --> 00:24:13,240
The one who sang when she died?

262
00:24:14,979 --> 00:24:17,760
She sang in her heart, even as she died.

263
00:24:19,687 --> 00:24:21,873
That's why she became
the patron saint of music.

264
00:24:30,226 --> 00:24:32,074
If she sang in her heart,
who would hear it?

265
00:24:35,987 --> 00:24:37,520
God always hears us.

266
00:24:49,688 --> 00:24:51,292
Do you know every saint or something?

267
00:24:52,338 --> 00:24:53,338
Oops!

268
00:25:11,400 --> 00:25:12,440
"Tan Kham Wa Rak"

269
00:25:13,856 --> 00:25:15,666
"There is a truth I want you to know"

270
00:25:15,789 --> 00:25:17,904
"Meanings words seem to hold"

271
00:25:19,116 --> 00:25:20,680
What song is this? I've never heard it.

272
00:25:24,843 --> 00:25:29,506
Tan Kham Wa Rak. Tanrak.

273
00:25:34,997 --> 00:25:36,593
Why are you named Tanrak?

274
00:25:46,687 --> 00:25:47,687
Huh?

275
00:26:10,415 --> 00:26:12,482
So... Why are you named Tanrak?

276
00:26:18,175 --> 00:26:20,412
Tan, where's Kongdech?

277
00:26:21,459 --> 00:26:23,911
He's probably at the farm plot.

278
00:26:24,169 --> 00:26:25,600
Oh. I thought you were together.

279
00:26:26,298 --> 00:26:27,303
Come on, guys.

280
00:26:27,536 --> 00:26:29,200
Let's help Kong at the farm plot.

281
00:26:43,091 --> 00:26:44,691
My mom had a hard time having a child.

282
00:26:45,848 --> 00:26:47,120
So she came here to pray.

283
00:26:48,201 --> 00:26:51,398
When she had me, she named me...

284
00:26:52,388 --> 00:26:53,391
Tanrak.

285
00:26:55,218 --> 00:26:58,920
Because I was a symbol of the love

286
00:26:59,915 --> 00:27:01,000
the Holy Mother gave her.

287
00:27:19,986 --> 00:27:24,131
My mom offered this rosary herself.

288
00:27:27,701 --> 00:27:29,280
When I miss her,

289
00:27:30,892 --> 00:27:31,892
I come here.

290
00:27:34,998 --> 00:27:37,360
And I tell the Holy Mother…

291
00:27:39,043 --> 00:27:43,096
if I ever get to heaven,

292
00:27:44,848 --> 00:27:46,520
please take me to my parents.

293
00:28:06,984 --> 00:28:08,680
Next time I can come here with you.

294
00:28:25,570 --> 00:28:26,570
Tanrak,

295
00:28:28,158 --> 00:28:29,158
I'll help.

296
00:28:39,675 --> 00:28:42,480
Since when are Tan and Barth best buds?

297
00:28:42,926 --> 00:28:46,115
Yeah. When did they
become close friends, Kong?

298
00:28:47,903 --> 00:28:49,240
If you wanna know, ask them.

299
00:28:49,871 --> 00:28:52,720
Oh, Mr. Kong. I thought you'd know.

300
00:28:52,886 --> 00:28:54,600
You're Tan's closest friend, aren't you?

301
00:29:06,984 --> 00:29:08,016
Hello, Teacher.

302
00:29:08,268 --> 00:29:09,268
Hello.

303
00:29:09,734 --> 00:29:11,414
What? Where did it go?

304
00:29:13,024 --> 00:29:15,157
Boys, come help me look at this.

305
00:29:16,298 --> 00:29:17,298
Go.

306
00:29:17,439 --> 00:29:20,895
I'm trying to save it, but it won't work.
What do I do?

307
00:29:23,131 --> 00:29:24,570
It's gone now.

308
00:29:26,645 --> 00:29:28,425
- This drive can't burn discs.
- Oh.

309
00:29:28,768 --> 00:29:30,520
It's a CD-ROM. It only reads them.

310
00:29:31,672 --> 00:29:34,205
What? But I need to save it on a disc.

311
00:29:34,230 --> 00:29:35,118
How am I supposed to do that?

312
00:29:35,143 --> 00:29:36,680
Come look at it for me.

313
00:29:36,705 --> 00:29:37,720
Come here. Sit down.

314
00:29:41,275 --> 00:29:42,840
It won't save at all.

315
00:29:46,874 --> 00:29:49,635
Oh, the file's too big.

316
00:29:50,194 --> 00:29:51,863
You'll need to split it across two discs.

317
00:29:52,437 --> 00:29:55,290
Well, the academic department

318
00:29:55,315 --> 00:29:57,940
told us to stop submitting paper copies
and send files instead.

319
00:29:57,965 --> 00:30:00,698
And those are all the students' projects.

320
00:30:01,174 --> 00:30:02,600
I'm not very good at this.

321
00:30:03,083 --> 00:30:04,613
If your files disappear,

322
00:30:04,863 --> 00:30:07,459
I'm dead. Totally dead.

323
00:30:09,322 --> 00:30:11,840
They won't disappear. I saved them for you.

324
00:30:12,700 --> 00:30:15,100
Just please don't close the program.

325
00:30:15,342 --> 00:30:18,120
Oh. Okay.

326
00:30:20,103 --> 00:30:22,170
You've got potential, you know.

327
00:30:22,987 --> 00:30:25,480
If you ever change your mind about
pursuing the religious path,

328
00:30:25,505 --> 00:30:26,840
you could go into science.

329
00:30:27,049 --> 00:30:30,600
Or vocational college. Something practical.

330
00:30:31,009 --> 00:30:32,021
How does that sound?

331
00:30:32,477 --> 00:30:33,799
Let me finish Grade 12 first.

332
00:30:34,840 --> 00:30:36,520
I'm already too lazy for school as it is.

333
00:30:36,654 --> 00:30:37,847
Okay.

334
00:30:38,876 --> 00:30:41,607
Anyway, Tanrak,
how did you two become close?

335
00:30:41,812 --> 00:30:44,159
Oh, we're not close.

336
00:30:44,944 --> 00:30:45,944
Huh?

337
00:30:46,762 --> 00:30:47,885
I just felt sorry for him.

338
00:30:48,152 --> 00:30:49,477
He had no friends.

339
00:30:58,093 --> 00:30:59,706
The Mass has ended.

340
00:30:59,937 --> 00:31:02,270
Go in peace.

341
00:31:03,959 --> 00:31:08,506
♪ I will not fight alone ♪

342
00:31:10,107 --> 00:31:15,726
♪ You who conquered death and sin ♪

343
00:31:16,133 --> 00:31:21,040
♪ Walk right beside me ♪

344
00:31:27,873 --> 00:31:28,873
Oh!

345
00:31:34,182 --> 00:31:35,186
Who are they?

346
00:31:35,987 --> 00:31:37,885
Cherry and Oh.

347
00:31:38,308 --> 00:31:39,872
Childhood friends from my neighborhood.

348
00:31:42,218 --> 00:31:43,220
Really just friends?

349
00:31:51,634 --> 00:31:53,520
Cherry. Oh.

350
00:31:55,479 --> 00:31:56,483
How have you been?

351
00:31:57,156 --> 00:31:59,880
This is Barth. He just joined Grade 12.

352
00:32:01,396 --> 00:32:02,396
Hi.

353
00:32:03,472 --> 00:32:04,960
I'll go put my things away.

354
00:32:09,882 --> 00:32:11,621
You haven't been to church in ages.

355
00:32:11,760 --> 00:32:14,005
Yeah. I've been helping my mom at the shop.

356
00:32:14,566 --> 00:32:16,960
She's been seeing the doctor,

357
00:32:17,359 --> 00:32:18,523
so I had to cover for her.

358
00:32:19,754 --> 00:32:21,434
Is Auntie Tim doing okay?

359
00:32:22,227 --> 00:32:23,231
She's all right.

360
00:32:23,347 --> 00:32:24,357
Did you know?

361
00:32:24,447 --> 00:32:27,015
They're building a 7-Eleven
where your house was.

362
00:32:30,246 --> 00:32:31,445
They tore it down?

363
00:32:34,614 --> 00:32:35,654
How long ago?

364
00:32:35,789 --> 00:32:36,817
It's about to open.

365
00:32:36,984 --> 00:32:39,351
They demolished the house
and built the store so quickly.

366
00:32:42,130 --> 00:32:44,411
What about the rose apple tree next door?

367
00:32:45,589 --> 00:32:46,680
Is it still there?

368
00:32:48,360 --> 00:32:50,440
That tree died
before they even tore the house down.

369
00:32:53,611 --> 00:32:57,214
But do you remember
when we climbed that tree as kids?

370
00:32:58,034 --> 00:32:59,520
I fell, and it hurt like hell.

371
00:32:59,941 --> 00:33:03,400
My mom scolded me for a whole week.

372
00:33:06,937 --> 00:33:09,317
You seem a lot quieter now, Tanrak.

373
00:33:12,036 --> 00:33:13,036
Really?

374
00:33:13,806 --> 00:33:15,672
Yeah. More grown-up.

375
00:33:19,326 --> 00:33:20,640
We should go.

376
00:33:21,301 --> 00:33:22,301
See you.

377
00:34:15,906 --> 00:34:17,277
You guys go ahead.

378
00:34:17,499 --> 00:34:19,115
See you.

379
00:34:47,236 --> 00:34:48,683
I wondered where you disappeared to.

380
00:34:50,748 --> 00:34:51,758
What are you doing?

381
00:34:57,427 --> 00:34:59,080
Practicing for the Christmas party.

382
00:35:03,970 --> 00:35:04,970
Play for me.

383
00:35:08,232 --> 00:35:09,232
Sure.

384
00:35:25,131 --> 00:35:26,811
I said I was practicing.

385
00:35:39,652 --> 00:35:40,652
Tanrak.

386
00:35:43,872 --> 00:35:45,847
If something's stressing you out,
you can tell me.

387
00:35:46,643 --> 00:35:47,664
You know that, right?

388
00:35:51,492 --> 00:35:52,812
Come on. Teach me.

389
00:35:56,422 --> 00:35:57,430
How do you play?

390
00:35:58,030 --> 00:35:59,057
How do you play?

391
00:36:00,060 --> 00:36:02,600
Let's start with… C.

392
00:36:07,490 --> 00:36:08,490
C, huh?

393
00:36:11,286 --> 00:36:12,571
- What else?
- B minor.

394
00:36:14,022 --> 00:36:15,280
- Like this?
- Yes.

395
00:36:29,585 --> 00:36:30,585
Barth.

396
00:36:33,394 --> 00:36:34,603
You're such a tease.

397
00:36:36,804 --> 00:36:38,320
I never said I couldn't play.

398
00:36:38,782 --> 00:36:39,995
I just wanted you to teach me.

399
00:36:50,696 --> 00:36:51,912
Out of all the chords,

400
00:36:52,262 --> 00:36:53,280
which one do you like?

401
00:36:55,398 --> 00:36:57,890
Well... they all sound nice, don't they?

402
00:37:00,367 --> 00:37:03,520
No. Say you could choose only one chord

403
00:37:04,930 --> 00:37:05,977
for the rest of your life.

404
00:37:06,411 --> 00:37:07,433
Which one would it be?

405
00:37:10,331 --> 00:37:11,331
Probably...

406
00:37:14,058 --> 00:37:15,058
C.

407
00:37:26,618 --> 00:37:28,000
I thought you'd pick this one.

408
00:37:34,271 --> 00:37:35,311
It suits you.

409
00:37:37,740 --> 00:37:38,740
Really?

410
00:37:39,312 --> 00:37:41,440
So what note do you like?

411
00:37:45,072 --> 00:37:46,072
What note?

412
00:37:51,232 --> 00:37:52,232
This one.

413
00:38:01,580 --> 00:38:02,580
Why?

414
00:38:09,924 --> 00:38:10,924
It feels...

415
00:38:12,528 --> 00:38:13,568
out of place.

416
00:38:15,385 --> 00:38:16,720
Like it doesn't belong.

417
00:38:19,692 --> 00:38:21,640
Like it's somewhere it shouldn't be.

418
00:38:35,823 --> 00:38:38,640
How about we play that song?

419
00:38:59,278 --> 00:39:02,712
♪ There is a truth I want you to know ♪

420
00:39:03,300 --> 00:39:06,710
♪ Meanings many words seem to hold ♪

421
00:39:07,384 --> 00:39:10,788
♪ No matter how beautiful they may be ♪

422
00:39:11,566 --> 00:39:14,366
♪ They fall short of what you mean to me ♪

423
00:39:15,020 --> 00:39:18,480
♪ Everything I do for you ♪

424
00:39:19,016 --> 00:39:22,480
♪ May reflect what my heart holds true ♪

425
00:39:23,039 --> 00:39:26,194
♪ Maybe my eyes already show ♪

426
00:39:26,243 --> 00:39:28,920
♪ The feelings in my heart that flow ♪

427
00:39:29,659 --> 00:39:36,726
♪ But do you know it's so much more?

428
00:39:37,348 --> 00:39:42,607
♪ Things I would like to give to you ♪

429
00:39:45,880 --> 00:39:47,897
♪ I'd gather every star ♪

430
00:39:47,922 --> 00:39:51,520
♪ To show all the love I have for you ♪

431
00:39:51,843 --> 00:39:55,137
♪ And make every song belong to you ♪

432
00:39:55,287 --> 00:40:00,773
♪ To tell you I love you more
than words could say ♪

433
00:40:01,066 --> 00:40:02,604
♪ Through seasons change

434
00:40:02,890 --> 00:40:08,693
♪ I'll spend with you
my every single breath ♪

435
00:40:09,287 --> 00:40:12,210
♪ No words can replace ♪

436
00:40:12,620 --> 00:40:18,771
♪ What my heart means
when it says I love you ♪

437
00:40:19,463 --> 00:40:26,758
♪ Let this love song speak for my heart
which belongs only to you ♪

438
00:40:27,578 --> 00:40:33,620
♪ Let it be the promise of our love
until the time is through ♪

439
00:40:39,434 --> 00:40:41,285
♪ I'd gather every star ♪

440
00:40:41,412 --> 00:40:45,042
♪ To show all the love I have for you ♪

441
00:40:45,363 --> 00:40:48,683
♪ And make every song belong to you ♪

442
00:40:48,794 --> 00:40:54,333
♪ To tell you I love you more
than words could say ♪

443
00:40:54,608 --> 00:40:56,281
♪ Through seasons change ♪

444
00:40:56,436 --> 00:41:02,755
♪ I'll spend with you
my every single breath ♪

445
00:41:02,909 --> 00:41:05,596
♪ No words can replace ♪

446
00:41:06,209 --> 00:41:13,103
♪ What my heart means
when it says I love you ♪

447
00:41:13,142 --> 00:41:18,383
If I speak in the tongues
of men or of angels

448
00:41:18,888 --> 00:41:20,040
but do not have love,

449
00:41:20,978 --> 00:41:25,008
I am only a resounding gong
or a clanging cymbal.

450
00:41:35,199 --> 00:41:36,225
Because we're friends.

451
00:42:06,501 --> 00:42:07,501
Barth.

452
00:42:10,357 --> 00:42:11,510
What are you doing?

453
00:42:13,615 --> 00:42:14,960
I know who's lying now.

454
00:42:18,099 --> 00:42:19,240
Lying about what?

455
00:42:20,663 --> 00:42:21,920
The brain teaser.

456
00:42:23,093 --> 00:42:24,920
The Lost One, the Lover, and the Believer.

457
00:42:26,188 --> 00:42:27,201
I figured it out.

458
00:42:28,607 --> 00:42:29,680
What's the answer?

459
00:42:31,462 --> 00:42:33,142
- I think...
- Not ready to sleep yet, huh?

460
00:42:36,456 --> 00:42:37,625
Did it have to be now?

461
00:42:41,062 --> 00:42:42,240
I wanted to know now.

462
00:42:43,447 --> 00:42:44,447
Why?

463
00:42:46,119 --> 00:42:47,119
Why?

464
00:42:50,588 --> 00:42:53,562
Because now I'm being punished,
writing down saints' names in the cemetery.

465
00:42:57,656 --> 00:42:58,656
Hey.

466
00:43:05,770 --> 00:43:07,210
Did you hear that?

467
00:43:08,497 --> 00:43:09,889
I heard a weird sound.

468
00:43:26,199 --> 00:43:27,294
You're scared, aren't you?

469
00:43:30,222 --> 00:43:31,600
Then go by yourself.

470
00:43:33,444 --> 00:43:34,501
You have to come with me.

471
00:43:34,526 --> 00:43:35,561
You're being punished.

472
00:43:38,746 --> 00:43:40,320
There's nothing there. Don't be scared.

473
00:43:58,849 --> 00:44:01,240
Joanna Wattana.

474
00:44:06,449 --> 00:44:07,605
John the Baptist.

475
00:44:10,066 --> 00:44:12,840
Hey, that's my saint's name.

476
00:44:16,863 --> 00:44:18,310
What's up, John the Baptist Tanrak?

477
00:44:23,078 --> 00:44:24,078
You know,

478
00:44:25,096 --> 00:44:27,960
Master Phak wouldn't know
if we just made up saints' names.

479
00:44:32,577 --> 00:44:34,297
Yeah. True.

480
00:44:36,029 --> 00:44:37,640
What does Master Phak even do all day

481
00:44:39,112 --> 00:44:40,785
besides catching us doing wrong things?

482
00:44:43,473 --> 00:44:44,960
Master Phak is a good person.

483
00:44:46,018 --> 00:44:47,861
He's my spiritual mentor.

484
00:44:48,625 --> 00:44:50,840
He's not actually that strict.

485
00:44:53,467 --> 00:44:54,962
If you become a Master one day,

486
00:44:56,457 --> 00:44:57,640
who's gonna be scared of you?

487
00:45:00,956 --> 00:45:02,120
You look way too kind.

488
00:45:10,151 --> 00:45:11,151
Really?

489
00:45:15,940 --> 00:45:18,440
Nine... twenty.

490
00:45:20,726 --> 00:45:22,322
Done. Let's go.

491
00:45:24,102 --> 00:45:25,102
Hey, wait.

492
00:45:28,419 --> 00:45:29,600
Since we're already out,

493
00:45:30,997 --> 00:45:32,202
wanna sneak out for some roti?

494
00:45:39,959 --> 00:45:40,999
Don't tell me

495
00:45:41,889 --> 00:45:43,320
you've never snuck out of school.

496
00:45:56,324 --> 00:45:58,147
Seriously? Come with me.

497
00:46:07,404 --> 00:46:08,412
Then hold this for me.

498
00:46:27,268 --> 00:46:28,905
It's high. Give me a boost.

499
00:47:01,234 --> 00:47:02,514
One, two, three.

500
00:47:14,108 --> 00:47:15,152
You really won't come?

501
00:47:15,786 --> 00:47:17,553
Come on. I'll help you up.

502
00:47:35,977 --> 00:47:37,604
Then wait here. I'll be back soon.

503
00:48:01,190 --> 00:48:06,200
Lust means letting desire control us.

504
00:48:06,969 --> 00:48:09,000
What if you can't stop it?

505
00:48:27,269 --> 00:48:28,355
You really won't come?

506
00:48:28,917 --> 00:48:31,040
Come on. I'll help you up.

507
00:49:01,628 --> 00:49:04,386
Here. I bought this for you.

508
00:49:05,166 --> 00:49:06,166
Have some.

509
00:49:08,710 --> 00:49:10,507
Hurry up. I wanna sleep.

510
00:49:26,736 --> 00:49:27,736
Help me.

511
00:50:16,778 --> 00:50:17,778
Eat it.

512
00:50:51,253 --> 00:50:52,520
Hurry up. I need to pee.

513
00:50:56,246 --> 00:50:57,246
Here.

514
00:50:58,638 --> 00:50:59,638
Pee here.

515
00:51:02,041 --> 00:51:03,052
No need to be shy.

516
00:51:28,722 --> 00:51:29,722
Nice aim.

517
00:51:45,882 --> 00:51:47,216
The answer is the Lost One.

518
00:51:49,389 --> 00:51:51,221
Because the Lost One
always tells the truth.

519
00:57:52,220 --> 00:57:57,008
(Next Episode) When the human heart starts
beating, it naturally begins to seek love.

520
00:57:57,660 --> 00:57:58,660
Why?

521
00:57:58,684 --> 00:58:02,035
I just haven't seen you
smile in a long time.

522
00:58:06,277 --> 00:58:06,864
Barth!

523
00:58:06,889 --> 00:58:08,503
Barth is so cool.

524
00:58:08,896 --> 00:58:10,829
Do you think he likes Cherry?

525
00:58:11,098 --> 00:58:13,960
I don't know if he likes her,
but Cherry definitely likes Barth.

526
00:58:13,984 --> 00:58:19,306
But the question is: does every
kind of love bring us closer to Him?
